@women_in_exile Refugee women founded @women_in_exile in 2002 to fight for their rights.
“Breaking Borders to Build Bridges” brings together texts about fleeing, surviving, &amp; 20 years of organizing as a refugee women’s group fighting for freedom of movement &amp; the abolishment of all camps.
(4/4) https://t.co/xSBrngU9UA

@soshumanity_en Each time it is the courts’ turn to reiterate what should be obvious: rescuing is not a crime!
Every criminalization attempt against sea rescue organizations is exposed for what it is: unlawful.

